nars.util

Class ContinuousBag<E extends Item>

  • java.lang.Object
    • nars.util.ContinuousBag<E>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IBag<E>

    public class ContinuousBag<E extends Item>
extends java.lang.Object
implements IBag<E>
    A bag without discrete levels implemented as a sorted list, which is accessed according to a random probability curve. For example, the curve can be shaped to favor higher-priority items. This models, to a degree, the behavior of the original Bag Distributor. ContinuousBag does not consistently perform better than Bag and remains EXPERIMENTAL.
